RUNNING A VERILATOR SIMULATION
https://www.itsembedded.com/dhd/verilator_1/

$ verilator --Wall --trace --cc rst_sync.sv --exe tb_rst_sync.cpp
- (regenerates .mk files to include cpp test bench (with --exe tb_rst_sync.cpp))
- (--Wall turns on all C++ warnings)
- (--trace enables waveform tracing)

$ make -C obj_dir -f Vrst_sync.mk Vrst_sync
- builds the executable
- (-C obj_dir tells make to work in obj_dir)
- (then pass required makefile with -f Vrst_sync.mk)
- (tell make to build the target Vrst_sync -- name of compiled tb executable)
- if successful, there should be a Vrst_sync binary in obj_dir

$ ./obj_dir/Vrst_sync --> running the executable
- if successful, should create waveform.vcd

$ gtkwave waveform.vcd
- step 1: click on TOP
- step 2: click on a signal and ctrl+A
- step 3: click on append
- step 4: inspect waveforms
